Attention parents/guardians of AISD students:
Please look out for this letter in the mail next week. This is for all returning students. Once you receive your letter in the mail you will want to go to https://registration.powerschool.com/family/gosnap.aspx?action=25234&culture=en or aisdk12.org and click on the link. I will also send out a mass text with the link next week so you can save it in your phone. You will enter the snapcode assigned to your student, look over the information, update what needs to be updated, and Esign the permissions. Please also make sure you enter an email address as well. If by Wednesday you did not receive a snapcode letter please call the District Office 886-6332.

Thank you!!

Good afternoon RJES parents!
We would like that all parents that are dropping off their children to please take a look at the map, the drop off area is the parking lot that is facing the ocean.

Pre-K is the pink lane, all parents are to stop and walk their child(ren) to the Pre-K outside door to be screened at door #4

Kindergarten - 5th grades will be in the blue lane. Please stay in your vehicle and lane while your child exits your vehicle to proceed to the following doors to be screened: Door #3: K-2nd
Door #5: 3rd - 5th

Thank you for your patience and cooperation during this school year and we look forward to seeing your children!

AISD re: The State of Alaska/Public Assistance Letters/applications

***You can also text PBET to 907-891-8913 and follow the prompts if you're worried it will not be received before the deadline***

If you received this letter (see picture) & your child was an enrolled student at AISD during the last school year (2019-2020), then they meet the qualification of Free School Meals. Your application must be received by the Division of Public Assistance -Wasilla, by Aug. 31st. It can be faxed if you’re concerned it will not reach the office by the deadline. For further information see pictures of info sheets &/or contact the Division of Public Assistance

AISD is an equal opportunity provider

post_text:
Hey everyone!

We are really excited to see everyone tomorrow for the start of camp.

A couple things to note before camp starts:

1. Please enter from the Chiefs Locker room side of the high school. There will be stations set up to take temperatures and complete registration. We ask that you maintain appropriate social distancing practices inside the hallway.
2. Water fountains will be blocked so please make sure your athlete brings a water bottle.
3. Following each session, there will be a cleaning of equipment period.
4. All athletes must bring a mask.

We appreciate everyone’s cooperation and patience and are looking forward to an incredible couple weeks!

Nt’oyaxsn (thank you)

-Chris

For the last 2 weeks, Annette Islands School District Staff have been working on creating experiential learning activities for children and families that might have participated in the past the yearly Cultural Camp. Due to Covid-19, Cultural Camp Staff have been working on creating kits rather than having an "in person"camp. Families that ordered the kits may pick them up starting today until 3:00pm on Tuesday thru Thursday from 8:00am to noon.

The School District would like to thank the staff for the hard work, passion and effort that they have poured into this project. The staff included; Naomi Leask, David Nelson, Jennifer McCarty, Sandy King, Chelsee Cook and Kalen Edenshaw. Amanda Schooland and some youngins helped, too!

post_text:
Metlakatla Parents/ Guardians/ Fans:

ASAA has postponed the State Basketball and Cheer Championship Tournament to reduce the spread of the Coronavirus Disease 2019, COVID-19. They anticipate that a final decision about the tournament will be made by March 16th. Please see their statement on the ASAA website, www.asaa.org.

In addition, the Student Government Conference (AASG) has been canceled and it is likely that all school-sponsored competitions will also be canceled after March 14th.

We will provide official updates on Facebook as they become available concerning the tournament and the impact that this situation will have on AISD. Our main priority is the health and safety of our students, staff, and community. As always, thank you for your support. If you have any questions or concerns please contact the District at 907-886-6332 or by email at contactus@aisdk12.org.

Thank you,

Taw Lindsey,
Superintendent, AISD

Tongass Federal Credit Union's Soaring Student Sponsorship applications are now available. The TFCU Sponsorships are for current students that need financial assistance to be able to participate in school activities.

For example: A student who has been invited to compete at the state level for music or sports but needs financial help to go.

TFCU will review the applications submitted each month and approve as many as they can within their monthly budget. They will email all of the applicants to inform them of who received the sponsorships that month. If your student did not receive the sponsorship, they may resubmit their application (same one is fine) for the following month's sponsorship opportunities.

Please join us in congratulating Janelle Caspersen for receiving the 2020 Paraeducator of the Year Award from the State of Alaska Department of Health and Social Services. She has consistently demonstrated a strong work ethic, a strong connection to kids, and a willingness to take on new challenges. This award is well-deserved. She will be formally recognized at the Winter SPED Conference in Anchorage during this month.
**Way to go Janelle**
